\f2\b \cf2 Why the practice pipeline doesn't affect the atoms:
\f1\b0 \
The 204 practice items fill EXERCISE slots as a backstop when no per-persona EXERCISE atoms exist. Your STORY atoms (RECOGNITION, MECHANISM_PROOF, TURNING_POINT, EMBODIMENT) are a completely separate pool. The practice selector and prose resolver don't touch STORY atoms at all. Nothing I wrote conflicts with or gets replaced by the practice library.\

\f2\b Why the old chat specs don't break the atoms either:
\f1\b0 \
The 12 structural archetypes, journey-shape variation, motif banks, and reframe-line systems are all assembly-level and arc-level decisions \'97 they govern how atoms get sequenced and arranged, not what the atoms contain. The arc YAML already has a\'a0
\f0\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf7 \cb8 \strokec7 motif:
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \'a0field (primary_symbol, recurring_image, tonal_signature) that the compiler uses for thematic selection. The atoms themselves don't need motif tags to participate \'97 they get selected by slot type, BAND range, MECHANISM_DEPTH, and topic/engine match. What the old specs describe adds variation at a layer above the atoms.\

\f2\b The one real gap:
\f1\b0 \
The reframe-line system is interesting because reframe lines are most naturally embedded in TURNING_POINT and EMBODIMENT blocks \'97 which is exactly where the atoms are doing their heaviest lifting. The atoms I wrote do have reframes, but they're narrative reframes baked into the prose, not tagged or extractable as standalone reframe lines. If the system later wants to inject reframe lines as a separate slot type or as a tagged metadata field, that would be additive work. Nothing breaks \'97 it just wouldn't be queryable as a distinct bank.\

\f2\b What actually closes the remaining gap given these updates:
\f1\b0 \
The practice library fills EXERCISE. STORY is complete. The outstanding non-STORY work now reduces to: REFLECTION atoms, INTEGRATION atoms, and HOOK/SCENE atoms per persona \'d7 topic. The old chat specs suggest REFLECTION and INTEGRATION should carry F1-F5 variant coverage and structural archetype awareness \'97 which means those atoms, when you write them, should be written with that architecture in mind rather than the same 20-block STORY format.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

