\f1 \cf2 Yes \'97 that's the gap. I only wrote STORY atoms. Here's what a compiled book actually contains vs. what exists:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 What's in a book (all slot types):
\f1\b0 \
STORY atoms are the narrative core \'97 the 140-200 word scenes that carry the emotional arc. Those are done, 134 files.\
But a book also has HOOK (chapter opening \'97 the first thing a reader hits), SCENE (sensory grounding moment, different from story), REFLECTION (the author's teaching voice, stepping outside the narrative to name what just happened), INTEGRATION (the closing of each chapter \'97 how the reader carries it forward), EXERCISE (practice), and COMPRESSION (distilled insight, 40-120 words, used in shorter formats).\

\f2\b What exists beyond STORY:
\f1\b0 \
Only one persona \'d7 topic has any of these:\'a0
\f0\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf7 \cb8 \strokec7 gen_z_professionals/anxiety
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \'a0has HOOK, SCENE, REFLECTION, EXERCISE files. INTEGRATION exists nowhere. COMPRESSION exists only for gen_z/burnout (2 files). The practice library backstop covers EXERCISE slots from the somatic library, but that's generic \'97 not persona-specific or topic-specific prose.\

\f2\b What that means for books:
\f1\b0 \
Right now the compiler fills missing non-STORY slots with placeholders. So books compile but they're skeleton books \'97 story scenes with empty chapter openings, no teaching voice, no integration closes. The STORY prose I wrote is the right quality and will hold up. But a reader opening a rendered book today would get full story scenes surrounded by placeholder text.\

\f2\b The old_chat_specs variation systems
\f1\b0 \'a0(archetypes, motifs, reframe lines, journey shapes) mostly affect REFLECTION and INTEGRATION \'97 those are where the author voice lives, where reframes get delivered, where motifs get named and returned. Without REFLECTION and INTEGRATION atoms, that whole variation layer has nothing to operate on.\
So: STORY is solid. The book is missing its framing, teaching voice, and chapter architecture prose. Want me to start writing REFLECTION and INTEGRATION atoms next? That's the highest-leverage gap.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

