\f1 \cf2 Here's exactly what the non-STORY slots are, what exists, and what's missing:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 The six-slot system
\f1\b0 \'a0(every chapter in a compiled book pulls from all six):\

\f2\b HOOK
\f1\b0 \'a0\'97 2nd person, \uc0\u8804 3 sentences, no questions, body anchor, open ending. Chapter opening that names the reader's state without explaining it.\'a0
\f3\i "You did everything they said to do. Your chest has not gotten the memo."
\f1\i0 \'a0Exists only for gen_z \'d7 anxiety (30 versions).\

\f2\b SCENE
\f1\b0 \'a0\'97 2nd person sensory present tense, zero emotion words, ends on action or sensation. Pure environmental grounding \'97 badge beeps, shoulder aches, elevator hum. Uses location tokens like\'a0
\f0\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf7 \cb8 \strokec7 \{street_name\}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 . Exists only for gen_z \'d7 anxiety (30 versions).\

\f2\b REFLECTION
\f1\b0 \'a0\'97 1st person author voice, 200-500 words, names the mechanism, delivers no fix, open ending. This is where the teaching lives \'97 the essay that explains\'a0
\f3\i why
\f1\i0 \'a0the pattern works the way it does. Exists only for gen_z \'d7 anxiety (30 versions).\

\f2\b EXERCISE
\f1\b0 \'a0\'97 2nd person imperative, explicit counts, \uc0\u8804 10 words per instruction, somatic, desk-compatible. No options, no modifications \'97 every instruction is mandatory. Exists only for gen_z \'d7 anxiety (30 versions) + practice library backstop (204 generic items).\

\f2\b INTEGRATION
\f1\b0 \'a0\'97 1st person quiet, 100-200 words, concrete, no resolution promise. Lands the chapter. Carry lines max 8 words:\'a0
\f3\i "Still here. Feet on floor."
\f1\i0 \'a0
\f2\b Exists nowhere \'97 not authored for any persona or topic.
\f1\b0 \

\f2\b What the formats actually require
\f1\b0 \'a0(k-minimums per slot): F006 (Nervous System Ladder) needs 12 of every type. F001 (90-Day) needs 15 HOOK, 20 SCENE, 90 STORY, 20 REFLECTION, 8 EXERCISE, 10 INTEGRATION. Right now every format except gen_z \'d7 anxiety compiles with placeholders in all five non-STORY slots.\

\f2\b What's needed for real books across all personas:
\f1\b0 \
For each of the 32 persona \'d7 topic pairs you want to ship, you need ~30 atoms per non-STORY slot type. That's roughly 30 HOOK + 30 SCENE + 30 REFLECTION + 30 EXERCISE + 30 INTEGRATION = 150 non-STORY atoms per pair, across 32 pairs = ~4,800 atoms. The STORY atoms you have are the foundation \'97 this is the layer that goes on top and makes books feel like actual books rather than assembled scenes.\
INTEGRATION is the most urgent gap because the emotional_role_slot_requirements spec says the\'a0
\f0\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf7 \cb8 \strokec7 integration
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \'a0chapter role\'a0
\f3\i requires
\f1\i0 \'a0an INTEGRATION slot \'97 meaning books literally cannot properly close their final chapter without it, for any persona or topic.\
Want me to start writing? REFLECTION and INTEGRATION are highest leverage \'97 REFLECTION because it carries the teaching voice for all 8 variation systems (motifs, reframes, archetypes all live there), INTEGRATION because it's the only completely empty slot across the entire corpus. I'd suggest starting with one or two persona \'d7 topic pairs at full depth rather than thin coverage across all 32.\
