\cb3 # 14. Emotional Force Thresholds\cb1 \
\cb3 Structural validation ensures correct build. Emotional force validation ensures the book moves the listener.\cb1 \
\cb3 ## 14.1 Chapter Temperature Classification\cb1 \
\cb3 | Phase | Temperature | Intensity | Requirements |\
|-------|-------------|-----------|--------------|\
| HARDSHIP | Hot | 4\'965 | Grounding verbs, body states, visible consequence |\
| HELP | Warm | 2\'963 | Teaching clarity, mechanism naming |\
| HEALING | Warm-Hot | 3\'964 | Emergence verbs, sensory present, no resolution |\
| HOPE | Cool | 1\'962 | Integration, quiet, synthesis |\cb1 \
\cb3 ## 14.2 HARDSHIP Chapter Requirements (Hot)\cb1 \
\cb3 **Grounding verbs (\uc0\u8805  2):** collapse, shatter, fragment, dissolve, abandon, crumble, unravel, break, fall, lose.\cb1 \
\cb3 **Body state words (\uc0\u8805  2):** tight, numb, hollow, frozen, raw, clenched, heavy, empty, small, trapped.\cb1 \
\cb3 **Visible consequence required.** HARDSHIP chapters cannot end with "and everything was okay." Something must change, break, or stop.\cb1 \
\cb3 **Gate E01:** Grounding verbs < 2 \uc0\u8594  hard fail.\
**Gate E02:** Body state words < 2 \uc0\u8594  warn.\
**Gate E03:** Ending feels resolved \uc0\u8594  flag for rewrite.\cb1 \
\cb3 ## 14.3 HEALING Chapter Requirements (Warm-Hot)\cb1 \
\cb3 **Emergence verbs (\uc0\u8805  2):** soften, open, return, notice, allow, settle, land, release, breathe, feel.\cb1 \
\cb3 **Sensory present words (\uc0\u8805  3):** breath, skin, ground, warmth, weight, texture, contact, sound, pulse, surface.\cb1 \
\cb3 **No resolution allowed.** HEALING chapters cannot end with transformation complete.\cb1 \
\cb3 **Gate E04:** Emergence verbs < 2 \uc0\u8594  warn.\
**Gate E05:** Sensory words < 3 \uc0\u8594  hard fail.\
**Gate E06:** Chapter ending implies cure \uc0\u8594  flag.\cb1 \
