\cb3 # 15. Spiritual Authenticity Gates\cb1 \
\cb3 Protection against spiritual clich\'e9s, abstract drift, and voice contamination.\cb1 \
\cb3 ## 15.1 Clich\'e9 Density Threshold\cb1 \
\cb3 No chapter may contain > 2 monitored clich\'e9 phrases.\cb1 \
\cb3 **Monitored:** "Everything happens for a reason," "Trust the universe," "Divine timing," "Holding space," "Sacred container," "Come into alignment," "Do the work," "Sit with" (overused), "Embodiment" (> 3x/chapter), "Nervous system" (> 4x/chapter without fresh context).\cb1 \
\cb3 **Gate S01:** > 2 phrases per chapter \uc0\u8594  hard fail.\
**Gate S02:** Phrase in > 30% of catalog \uc0\u8594  warn.\cb1 \
\cb3 **Exception:** Clich\'e9 allowed if immediately followed by grounding/specificity, or if doctrine-locked for that teacher.\cb1 \
\cb3 ## 15.2 Abstract Noun Ceiling\cb1 \
\cb3 Max 8 abstract nouns per 200 words. Monitored: consciousness, awareness, presence, energy, frequency, vibration, alignment, wholeness, integration, embodiment, authenticity.\cb1 \
\cb3 **Gate S03:** > 8 per 200 words \uc0\u8594  warn. > 12 \u8594  hard fail.\cb1 \
\cb3 ## 15.3 Teacher Voice Bleed Detection\cb1 \
\cb3 If Teacher A's signature phrase appears in Teacher B's book \uc0\u8594  contamination.\cb1 \
\cb3 **Gate S04:** Signature phrase from another teacher \uc0\u8594  hard fail.\cb1 \
\cb3 ## 15.4 Specificity Requirement\cb1 \
\cb3 Every teacher must demonstrate specific knowledge. Generic ("The body holds wisdom") fails. Specific ("The psoas muscle holds the memory of running. When you freeze, it contracts...") passes.\cb1 \
\cb3 **Gate S05:** Human review. Generic/vague teaching without grounding \uc0\u8594  flag.\cb1 \
