\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 what do you think of this:\'a0in book planning, the writer is writing prose:  HOOK, SCENE, REFLECTION, EXERCISE, INTEGRATION is that too inflexible? does it mean every chapter has a exercise? do we change this around in our code so it doesn't feel like template or get spam flags? desc what is and what options \
Current setup is flexible enough if used correctly, but it can feel templated if every chapter always keeps the same full slot set.\
What it means now:\
1. Your default chapter template is HOOK, SCENE, STORY, REFLECTION, EXERCISE, INTEGRATION (plus optional COMPRESSION in some formats).\
2. No, it should not mean every chapter must have a \'93full\'94 exercise block. Exercise can be optional/light/short by chapter role and book size.\
3. Spam risk comes from repeated structure + repeated phrasing + repeated ordering, not from slot names alone.\
Best options (ranked):\
1. Keep slot architecture, vary presence/weight by chapter role (recommended).\
   * Some chapters: no EXERCISE.\
   * Some: micro-exercise (1\'963 lines).\
   * Some: full practice.\
   * Enforce per-book quotas, not per-chapter uniformity.\
2. Enable positional variation safely (you already have this pattern in old specs).\
   * Reorder compatible slots by mode.\
   * Keep invariants: opener first, takeaway/integration constraints, practice block rules.\
   * This reduces \'93same cadence\'94 signatures.\
3. Use chapter archetypes\
   * Example types: HOOK_HEAVY, MECHANISM_HEAVY, PRACTICE_HEAVY, INTEGRATION_HEAVY.\
   * Map each archetype to a slot policy and word budget.\
   * Prevents every chapter feeling identical.\
4. Add duration/size rules\
   * Short book: max 1 full exercise total.\
   * Mid: 2\'963 exercises.\
   * Full: 3\'965 exercises.\
   * This is a major anti-template control.\
5. Inject micro-variants\
* opener/bridge/closer pools and F1\'96F5 families for HOOK/SCENE/REFLECTION/INTEGRATION.\
* Reduces repeated section fingerprints.\
What to change in code (practical):\
1. Move from \'93fixed slot list per chapter\'94 to \'93chapter archetype -> slot policy\'94.\
2. Add exercise_mode per chapter (none | micro | full) with quota validator.\
3. Add section_reorder_mode with semantic safety checks.\
4. Add planner novelty scoring so repeated chapter signatures are penalized.\
5. Keep deterministic selection and hard CI thresholds for clustering.\
Bottom line:\
* Keep the architecture, but stop rendering every chapter with the same full slot pattern.\
* Vary slot presence, exercise depth, and order by chapter role/size/arc.\
* That gives authored feel and lowers spam-pattern risk without throwing away your system.\cb1 \
