How the Planner Selects Knobs\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f6\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf7 \cb8 \strokec7 phoenix_v4/planning/variation_selector.py
\f0\fs24 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0follows this algorithm:\
1. Fixed inputs:\'a0persona_id, topic_id, engine_id(s), format_id, seed, series_id\
2. Build compatible candidates\'a0for each knob (filtered by topic compatibility, duration compatibility)\
3. Score each candidate combination:\
   * Compatibility score (topic \'d7 knob fit)\
   * Narrative quality score (journey_shape \'d7 chapter_archetype coherence)\
   * Anti-cluster penalty from wave index (penalize combos used in recent waves)\
   * Series diversity penalty (penalize combos used by other installments in same series)\
4. Apply hard caps:\'a0No combo may exceed 15% of total catalog. No knob value may exceed 30% of wave.\
5. Deterministic selection:\'a0Top-scoring combination wins. Stable tie-break by seed.\
6. Persist:\'a0Write variation_signature + all knob values to plan output and similarity index.\
The First 30 Seconds Spec (Spotify Conversion Surface)\
Research shows that on Spotify, three "weak signals" predict whether a listener will initiate a full stream:\'a0follow,\'a030-second preview listen, and\'a0intent-to-pay. The 30-second sample is the single highest-leverage conversion surface across all platforms.\
Every book's opening must be engineered as a conversion surface, not just a chapter introduction.\
yaml\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f6\fs21 \cf10 \cb13 \strokec10 # config/production/first_30_seconds_spec.yaml\
first_30_seconds:\
  required_elements:\
    - element: problem_statement\
      timing: "0:00-0:10"\
      description: >\
        Name the listener's problem in their language.\
        Use consumer_language_map.yaml terms, not clinical terms.\
        Example: "You know that thing where your brain won't shut off\
        at 2am \'97 where you replay the conversation, rehearse the apology,\
        and plan for disasters that never come?"\
\
    - element: immediate_tool_preview\
      timing: "0:10-0:20"\
      description: >\
        Preview the shift the book delivers. Concrete, not promissory.\
        Example: "This book gives you a way to interrupt the loop \'97\
        not by fighting it, but by understanding why it's running."\
\
    - element: tone_trust_cue\
      timing: "0:20-0:30"\
      description: >\
        Establish narrator credibility and warmth. Listener must feel\
        "this person understands me" within 30 seconds.\
        Human narration: vocal warmth, measured pace, no rush.\
        AI narration: natural cadence, zero robotic artifacts.\
\
  validation_rules:\
    - No exercise instructions in first 30 seconds (too soon for trust)\
    - No series references or "in this book you'll learn" lists\
    - No credentials dump (author bio comes later)\
    - Problem statement must use consumer_language_map terms\
    - Must match persona voice_tone and pace_bpm from persona config\
    - Must pass persona specificity score >= 0.70\
\
  platform_specific:\
    spotify:\
      notes: >\
        First 30s IS the preview sample \'97 this is the conversion surface.\
        Design for earbuds during commute (not quiet room).\
        Include a save/follow prompt within first 10 minutes.\
        Skip rate feeds taste profile \'97 strong openings reduce skips.\
    google_play:\
      notes: >\
        Preview is configurable (20-100% of content).\
        First chapter is the de facto preview \'97 make it complete.\
    audible:\
      notes: >\
        Sample is typically ~5 minutes \'97 first 30s is the hook within that.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

