14. Summary\
The catalog is 1,008 standalone books organized into overlapping series.\'a0Each book owns a search term, targets a specific persona, and delivers a complete therapeutic journey. No book depends on any other book.\
Three models layer to maximize variety while minimizing writing:\
* Model A (topic) provides the spine \'97 12 topics with distinct engines\
* Model C (persona) provides the multiplier \'97 10 personas with distinct voices\
* Model B (depth) provides the curriculum \'97 Tier 1 topics get Foundations + Advanced\
Seven variation knobs ensure structural uniqueness:book_structure_id, journey_shape_id, chapter_archetypes, section_reorder_mode, motif_id, reframe_profile_id \uc0\u8594  variation_signature\
Five enforcement levels prevent repetition:\'a0within-book, within-series, within-wave, catalog-wide, market-level\
Title = search keyword. Subtitle = persona hook.\'a0Generated from templates. Every book gets a unique, market-ready title+subtitle combination.\
The first 30 seconds of every book is a conversion surface.\'a0Problem statement \uc0\u8594  tool preview \u8594  tone trust cue, engineered for Spotify's preview-to-stream funnel. This is the highest-leverage production spec in the system.\
Narration follows revenue logic.\'a0Human narration for Tier 1 flagships and high-trust topics (somatic, sleep, grief). AI narration for variants, short-form, and Gen Alpha. AI narration willingness is declining \'97 treat voice trust as a conversion variable, not just a cost variable.\
Platform rules are system rules.\'a0Google Play promo mechanics (scheduled discounts, promo codes, series bundles) and Spotify discovery signals (search/listen/skip/save \uc0\u8594  taste profile) are built into the distribution config, not left to marketing. Release scheduling, file naming, and preorder pipeline are automated across 24 brands.\
Compliance is a lint layer, not a disclaimer.\'a0FTC health claims rules, platform content policies, and therapeutic guardrails (polyvagal framing, habit formation timelines, depression safety) are enforced at the content generation level through banned phrases, required disclaimers, and safe positioning language. "Not medical advice" disclaimers do not fix implied cure claims \'97 the content itself must be clean.\
Revenue-tiered personas drive production priority:\'a0Build for millennial women, tech/finance, and entrepreneurs first (60% of addressable revenue). Existing Gen Z and healthcare atoms provide Tier 3 catalog depth immediately.\
The catalog grows multiplicatively while writing effort grows additively.\'a0Mechanisms are authored once. Engines once per topic. Templates once per persona. Variables once per persona \'d7 location. Atoms are the main writing \'97 constrained by everything above to ~60% less effort per atom than free-writing.\cb1 \
