\f2\b \cf2 The Gate 15 fix is a big deal.
\f1\b0 \'a0Before, if a book failed to compile because a chapter needed a BAND: 4 STORY atom in, say,\'a0
\f0\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf7 \cb8 \strokec7 anxiety/shame
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \'a0and none existed, you just got a pipeline failure with no direction. Now it says exactly which band is missing for which chapter. That turns a debugging session into a content ticket. Very useful.\

\f2\b What the spec is actually asking me to do:
\f1\b0 \
The core problem it's solving is band clustering. When I write ENGINE files, I assign BAND values \'97 but I may have written 14 BAND: 3 stories and 6 BAND: 4 with zero BAND: 1 or 2. If the arc planner routes a chapter to BAND: 1 (a low-intensity emotional entry), nothing's available and the compile fails. The fix is: every engine pool needs at least 2 atoms at each of the 5 bands.\
The\'a0
\f0\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf7 \cb8 \strokec7 SEMANTIC_FAMILY
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \'a0field is new metadata I haven't been adding. It's a second clustering dimension \'97 so the anti-spam logic can check both band variety AND narrative family variety when selecting stories for a book.\
The anti-cluster requirements (F1\'96F5 spread, no repeated openers/closers, rotating motifs) are things I've been doing editorially but without explicit tags. Now they need to be enforceable.\

\f2\b Is it helpful? Yes, with one caveat.
\f1\b0 \
